    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="doc" xml:id="AmbiguousNames_example">


                <div type="docbody">
                    <p>A person, Sally, is mentioned. The transcriber knows that it could be either
                            <persRef xml:id="auntSally">Aunt Sally</persRef> or <persRef
                            xml:id="cousinSally">Cousin Sally</persRef> based on context but can't
                        be sure which.</p>

                    <p>The transcriber can use the note structure to document their
                        domain-knowledge and link to the possible candidates. This method will
                        explicitly state the transcriber's knowledge while acknowledging a degree of
                        uncertainty. Later work might be able to determine which "Sally" is being
                        referenced and revise the document accordingly.</p>
                </div>


                <div type="docback">
                    <note type="gloss">
                        <p><persRef ref="sally-unknown01">Sally</persRef> most likely refers to
                            <persRef ref="aunt-sally">Aunt Sally</persRef> or <persRef
                                ref="cousin-sally">Cousin Sally</persRef>.</p>
                    </note>
                </div>


            </div>
        </body>
